231
00:12:07,119 --> 00:12:08,986
‐Shogun‐‐
‐Don't bother.

232
00:12:09,019 --> 00:12:10,152
‐Suezo: I think he's serious.

233
00:12:10,186 --> 00:12:14,086
‐Prepare for a taste
of my lightning sword.

234
00:12:14,119 --> 00:12:15,519
‐Wait. Don't do it.

235
00:12:27,252 --> 00:12:29,286
‐Shogun: (chuckles awkwardly)
I‐‐

236
00:12:32,319 --> 00:12:35,519
Oh, seven‐in‐one warrior,
only the greatest soldiers

237
00:12:35,552 --> 00:12:37,152
have ever stopped
my lightning sword.

238
00:12:37,186 --> 00:12:39,786
‐What's this "seven‐in‐one
warrior" stuff anyway?

239
00:12:39,819 --> 00:12:42,986
‐Stop feigning innocence!
Ring of steel!

240
00:12:45,686 --> 00:12:48,386
Oh, it must have been weakened
from the years in ice.

241
00:12:48,419 --> 00:12:51,552
Well, a broken sword
isn't enough to stop
Shogun the mighty.

242
00:12:57,086 --> 00:12:58,519
(panting)

243
00:12:59,819 --> 00:13:02,086
Strange, how easily
you avoided my sword.

244
00:13:02,119 --> 00:13:04,886
‐It wasn't that hard,
seeing as it's only
a foot long.

245
00:13:04,919 --> 00:13:06,986
‐Shogun,
what's gotten into you?

246
00:13:07,019 --> 00:13:08,886
‐Shogun: Enough idle chatter!

247
00:13:08,919 --> 00:13:10,486
‐Stumble Samurai.

248
00:13:13,886 --> 00:13:15,986
‐Huh? Tiger!

249
00:13:16,019 --> 00:13:17,986
‐Words won't get through to him.

250
00:13:18,019 --> 00:13:19,919
‐(Shogun laughing)
‐All: Huh?

251
00:13:19,952 --> 00:13:23,952
‐Seven‐in‐one warrior,
at last you have
revealed yourself.

252
00:13:23,986 --> 00:13:26,352
The duel has just begun.

253
00:13:26,386 --> 00:13:29,786
Prepare for my
whirlwind attack!

254
00:13:32,986 --> 00:13:34,186
‐Are you okay?

255
00:13:34,219 --> 00:13:38,686
‐(groaning) My reputation,
it falls into disrepair.

256
00:13:38,719 --> 00:13:40,186
How utterly frustrating.

257
00:13:40,219 --> 00:13:41,919
‐He's pathetic.

258
00:13:41,952 --> 00:13:43,719
‐All: Shogun?

259
00:13:43,752 --> 00:13:45,252
‐Shogun: Unhand me.

260
00:13:45,286 --> 00:13:47,586
A great soldier knows
when to admit defeat.

261
00:13:47,619 --> 00:13:50,452
But you can never destroy
my pride.

262
00:13:50,486 --> 00:13:53,986
‐Get a grip, Shogun.
‐Quit acting weird!
Now, get up!

263
00:13:54,019 --> 00:13:55,986
‐Shogun the mighty, my foot.

264
00:13:56,019 --> 00:13:58,919
Zuums, just forget Shogun
and go after them yourselves.

265
00:14:01,352 --> 00:14:03,152
‐Mocchi: Baddies‐chi.

266
00:14:03,186 --> 00:14:05,719
‐Golem, you stay here
and protect Holly and Shogun.

267
00:14:05,752 --> 00:14:07,019
‐Golem: Goh.

268
00:14:11,319 --> 00:14:13,686
‐Tiger: Lightning attack!

269
00:14:13,719 --> 00:14:15,686
‐Double pounder!
Double pounder!
Double pounder!

270
00:14:15,719 --> 00:14:17,652
‐Tongue slap!

271
00:14:22,986 --> 00:14:26,286
‐They've outnumbered us.
‐They just keep on coming.

272
00:14:26,319 --> 00:14:28,519
‐Let's bolt till we have a plan.
‐All: Yeah!

273
00:14:30,819 --> 00:14:32,819
‐Shogun: Unhand me, you brute.

274
00:14:32,852 --> 00:14:34,119
‐After them!

275
00:14:44,222 --> 00:14:47,356
What? You still
haven't found them?

276
00:14:51,922 --> 00:14:54,322
‐Is the coast clear?
‐Bad news‐chi.

277
00:14:54,356 --> 00:14:56,122
‐They've got us
completely surrounded.

278
00:14:56,156 --> 00:14:58,822
‐Then we'll have to sit tight
and try waiting them out.

279
00:14:58,856 --> 00:15:01,856
Tiger should be back
fairly soon.
‐Genki: Hmm.

280
00:15:03,122 --> 00:15:05,056
Any progress?
‐Mmm‐mmm.

281
00:15:05,089 --> 00:15:06,922
‐Stubborn man here won't budge.

282
00:15:06,956 --> 00:15:08,622
‐End the duel
and have your victory.

283
00:15:08,656 --> 00:15:11,256
‐Come on, Shogun,
it was a one‐way fight
in the first place.

284
00:15:11,289 --> 00:15:14,156
‐Shogun: A duel is a battle
for one's integrity and pride.

285
00:15:14,189 --> 00:15:18,756
No, take your victory
and let me proceed down the road
of failure and ridicule.

286
00:15:18,789 --> 00:15:21,289
‐Even if you did lose,
that's no reason to give up.

287
00:15:21,322 --> 00:15:23,322
You can always train
and have another duel.

288
00:15:23,356 --> 00:15:27,089
‐Shogun: Black Lightning
being retrained like
a mere apprentice?

289
00:15:27,122 --> 00:15:30,456
(scoffs) Such an undignified act
I could not commit.

290
00:15:33,889 --> 00:15:36,756
‐So what if it's undignified?
‐Shogun: Hmm?

291
00:15:36,789 --> 00:15:38,789
‐You might not agree,

292
00:15:38,822 --> 00:15:42,022
but to me, what matters
is having the courage
to never give up.

293
00:15:42,056 --> 00:15:43,722
That's more important
than winning.

294
00:15:46,922 --> 00:15:48,022
‐(Shogun chuckles)

295
00:15:49,089 --> 00:15:50,822
What do you know about it?

296
00:15:50,856 --> 00:15:53,422
You don't understand
what it means to be known

297
00:15:53,456 --> 00:15:55,889
as the mightiest warrior
in the land.

298
00:15:56,989 --> 00:15:58,089
‐I'm sorry.

299
00:16:00,189 --> 00:16:02,189
‐Huh? What did you find out?

300
00:16:02,222 --> 00:16:04,356
‐There's a rocky stretch
not far up ahead.

301
00:16:04,389 --> 00:16:06,689
I think we can lose them
once we get past it.

302
00:16:06,722 --> 00:16:08,856
‐Well, then let's make
a run for it.

303
00:16:08,889 --> 00:16:10,256
‐Holly: Yeah.
‐Chi!

304
00:16:10,289 --> 00:16:12,256
‐Well, shall we go?

305
00:16:12,289 --> 00:16:15,656
Huh?
‐Shogun: Go on without me.

306
00:16:15,689 --> 00:16:17,189
‐But Shogun‐‐

307
00:16:17,222 --> 00:16:19,322
‐You heard what the man said.
Let's leave him.

308
00:16:19,356 --> 00:16:22,256
‐We can't.
‐It's us the Baddies are after,
not Shogun,

309
00:16:22,289 --> 00:16:24,189
so there's no sense
worrying about him.

310
00:16:26,222 --> 00:16:28,989
‐Let's get going.
‐Uh, yeah. Sure.

311
00:16:40,956 --> 00:16:44,389
What matters is having
the courage to never give up.

312
00:16:44,422 --> 00:16:46,689
That's more important
than winning.

313
00:16:48,122 --> 00:16:50,756
‐Shogun: 9,995.

314
00:16:50,789 --> 00:16:53,056
9,996.

315
00:16:54,356 --> 00:16:57,456
9,997.

316
00:16:57,489 --> 00:16:59,889
9,998.

317
00:17:01,189 --> 00:17:04,022
9,999.

318
00:17:04,056 --> 00:17:06,189
(groaning)

319
00:17:15,289 --> 00:17:17,522
10,001.

320
00:17:18,722 --> 00:17:20,922
10,002.

321
00:17:20,956 --> 00:17:22,322
10,003.

322
00:17:25,922 --> 00:17:29,389
Now I have the true spirit
of a warrior.

323
00:17:31,956 --> 00:17:33,556
‐Zuum: That way.

324
00:17:36,089 --> 00:17:39,122
‐Genki: It's a dead end.
‐(Mum Mew laughing)

325
00:17:40,789 --> 00:17:43,589
This time, you won't
get away, I'm afraid.

326
00:17:43,622 --> 00:17:46,622
It is only seven of you,
after all.

327
00:17:46,656 --> 00:17:49,322
We should have done things
this way from the start

328
00:17:49,356 --> 00:17:51,889
rather than counting on Shogun.
‐Gobi: Yeah.

329
00:17:51,922 --> 00:17:53,822
‐Huh?
What are you talking about?

330
00:17:53,856 --> 00:17:56,289
‐I heard the legends
of Shogun the mighty,

331
00:17:56,322 --> 00:17:59,056
so I gave him orders
to defeat you
and your friends,

332
00:17:59,089 --> 00:18:02,522
but unfortunately,
he turned out to be weaker
than I thought.

333
00:18:02,556 --> 00:18:03,922
‐So you sent him after us.

334
00:18:03,956 --> 00:18:05,922
‐(laughs)

335
00:18:05,956 --> 00:18:10,356
I have to say, it was nice
working with a monster
who was so gullible.

336
00:18:10,389 --> 00:18:12,756
‐You're despicable.
‐You mean‐chi.

337
00:18:12,789 --> 00:18:14,456
‐Sticks and stones, my friends.

338
00:18:14,489 --> 00:18:17,656
Now, how about handing over
that Mystery Disk?

339
00:18:18,956 --> 00:18:23,422
A long wait, but at last
the evil soul will be back
in our hands.

340
00:18:23,456 --> 00:18:28,922
And with it, the greatest power
and the key to allow the Baddies
to reign supreme!

341
00:18:28,956 --> 00:18:32,156
(laughing)
‐Shogun: So that was
your true motive.

342
00:18:33,389 --> 00:18:36,356
You still rely
on Moo's evil power,

343
00:18:36,389 --> 00:18:41,089
but the only invincible power
comes from within
after much training.

344
00:18:41,122 --> 00:18:42,756
Witness it firsthand!

345
00:18:42,789 --> 00:18:45,322
‐All: Shogun!
‐(laughing)

346
00:18:45,356 --> 00:18:47,456
Lookout, everyone,
he's got a big stick.

347
00:19:04,156 --> 00:19:05,389
After him!

348
00:19:10,456 --> 00:19:11,722
‐Shogun!

349
00:19:33,489 --> 00:19:36,389
‐The legendary
lightning flash technique.

350
00:19:36,422 --> 00:19:38,556
‐Whoa! I don't believe it!

351
00:19:38,589 --> 00:19:40,189
‐(Mum Mew whimpering)

352
00:19:45,389 --> 00:19:46,722
‐All: Shogun!

353
00:19:48,822 --> 00:19:49,889
‐(Shogun laughing)

354
00:19:51,156 --> 00:19:52,656
‐Genki: Thanks for
all your help, Shogun.

355
00:19:52,689 --> 00:19:55,356
‐Shogun: It is I who owes
a debt of gratitude.

356
00:19:55,389 --> 00:19:58,256
You made me remember
something very important.

357
00:19:58,289 --> 00:20:00,022
‐What's so important‐chi?

358
00:20:00,056 --> 00:20:04,256
‐To have passion and conviction,
and to never give up
on your dreams.

359
00:20:04,289 --> 00:20:05,989
‐Shogun.

360
00:20:06,022 --> 00:20:09,056
‐Shogun: Today,
I will train myself anew.

361
00:20:09,089 --> 00:20:12,922
And good luck to you
in the Legend Cup.
‐Mocchi: Chi.

362
00:20:12,956 --> 00:20:16,022
‐Shogun: I hope to challenge you
to another duel someday.

363
00:20:16,056 --> 00:20:20,756
Then, you must transform
yourselves and show me your
seven‐in‐one warrior techniques.

364
00:20:20,789 --> 00:20:22,256
‐All: Transform ourselves?

365
00:20:22,289 --> 00:20:25,789
‐Shogun: Farewell,
seven fierce warriors
who fight as one.

366
00:20:27,122 --> 00:20:29,222
‐Wait, Shogun.

367
00:20:29,256 --> 00:20:31,556
‐I think he's got us
mixed up with someone else.

368
00:20:31,589 --> 00:20:35,222
‐Yeah. But, hey, don't you think
it kind of suits us?

369
00:20:35,256 --> 00:20:36,856
‐We're veterans of many battles.

370
00:20:36,889 --> 00:20:39,222
Seven soldiers
who fight together as one.

371
00:20:39,256 --> 00:20:40,822
‐Genki: Hmm.
‐Yeah.

372
00:20:40,856 --> 00:20:43,756
‐Shogun, here's to making
dreams come true.

373
00:20:48,489 --> 00:20:50,922
‐♪ Mon‐mon‐mon‐monsters‐‐
Monsters rule ♪

374
00:20:50,956 --> 00:20:53,022
‐(theme music playing)

375
00:21:15,656 --> 00:21:17,322
‐♪ Monsters rule ♪

